[2026-03-30 21:33:23.120] [PRINT]         "body_full": "Get your todo list done faster with coding agent and agent mode     \r\n\r\n\u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c \u200c     \r\n\r\n\"GitHub\"                                  \"GitHub\"                                            <https://app.github.media/e/er?s=88570519&lid=263&elqTrackId=3beeddfb1037496e83f72d4bc926e898&elq=feb3b649ff7747a0b97f63294b1f7134&elqaid=4562&elqat=1&elqak=8AF537F69F9CEF578FC2281ECC1FF49AE04F6D0CDD03F7E7AC228343D54B8750E8D5>                            \r\n\r\nCopilot IRL                   \r\n-------------------------------------------------\r\nSo far we\u2019ve gone through how to set up Copilot Pro, tips for writing effective prompts, and choosing the right model for your job. Now, it\u2019s time to really dig into what Copilot can accomplish in your workflow \u2014 and see it in action.  \r\n\r\n\u26a1 Lightning fast foundations                           \r\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nBy asking Copilot to draft an issue, you can quickly design a clear plan for your project. Then you can assign that issue directly to the new GitHub Copilot coding agent, which will asynchronously work to execute on the task at hand and give you a PR.                         \r\n\r\nKick things off fast with Copilot <https://app.github.media/e/er?s=88570519&lid=8181&elqTrackId=160d63e42789402cb8fdef5e43f69efd&elq=feb3b649ff7747a0b97f63294b1f7134&elqaid=4562&elqat=1&elqak=8AF5BBBAFB26652DB0FA8FFEFEB15315A1306D0CDD03F7E7AC228343D54B8750E8D5>                                                            \r\n\r\n\ud83d\udd0d Review and refactor                           \r\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nIn any development project, maintaining a clean and efficient codebase is crucial for making future work easier. But in reality, things can quickly become messy when your priorities are elsewhere (it happens!). That\u2019s where Copilot can be useful. It doesn\u2019t just assist in writing code, it also makes the review and refactoring process smoother and more efficient. Here\u2019s how. \r\n\r\nReview and refactor with Copilot <https://app.github.media/e/er?s=88570519&lid=8180&elqTrackId=df72e1cf37064ef8b3b6bfca166de424&elq=feb3b649ff7747a0b97f63294b1f7134&elqaid=4562&elqat=1&elqak=8AF530FFDA51CF92DEB8EEFACED0F4A4D92D6D0CDD03F7E7AC228343D54B8750E8D5>                                                            \r\n\r\n\ud83e\udd16 Dig deeper into agent mode \r\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nGitHub Copilot agent mode is a synchronous collaborator that performs multi-step coding tasks based on natural-language prompts. More simply, it\u2019s a problem solver that understands your intent, builds a solution, and iterates until it gets things right. \r\n\r\nLearn more about agent mode <https://app.github.media/e/er?s=88570519&lid=8179&elqTrackId=dd4d0f4921e54ad38efd6a779e7cf5ca&elq=feb3b649ff7747a0b97f63294b1f7134&elqaid=4562&elqat=1&elqak=8AF5E0951E3B166EF568927C17A7AC3868DB6D0CDD03F7E7AC228343D54B8750E8D5>                                                            \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\"X\" <https://x.com/github?elqTrackId=088c53e52834499bbe48caebc5ea5a34&elq=feb3b649ff7747a0b97f63294b1f7134&elqaid=4562&elqat=1&elqCampaignId=4748&elqak=8AF57B6B90C7338035BE4705F4B72CF568E46D0CDD03F7E7AC228343D54B8750E8D5> \u200a \"Instagram\" <https://www.instagram.com/github/?elqTrackId=efe5410eae1342ed8c1456dbc3f8f8d7&elq=feb3b649ff7747a0b97f63294b1f7134&elqaid=4562&elqat=1&elqCampaignId=4748&elqak=8AF54DAE6EB2D143FDB99BD426E2936774F86D0CDD03F7E7AC228343D54B8750E8D5> \u200a \"YouTube\" <https://www.youtube.com/github?elqTrackId=4b1fbabe41ea4b43bf0e05719b1c8a9a&elq=feb3b649ff7747a0b97f63294b1f7134&elqaid=4562&elqat=1&elqCampaignId=4748&elqak=8AF56D83